{
  "texts": [
    "Ignoring the devotional advice of a supervisor can be morally wrong.",
    "Supervisors wish their subordinates to grow and succeed and are expected to provide more relevant advice.",
    "Therefore, ignoring your supervisor's advice is a disregard for his/her efforts and trust, and may undermine communication and teamwork in the workplace.",
    "The text suggests that the supervisor was dedicated to providing advice.",
    "However, because of the fact that the advice was ignored, this could be a morally or legally wrong act."
  ]
}